  "text": "In the neuromuscular junction, staurosporine blocks release of FM1-43 from synaptic vesicles pre-loaded with this membrane-staining dye, but does not block release of the endogenous neurotransmitter acetylcholine [CITATION_1] . This suggested that staurosporine interfered with the post-exocytotic collapse of synaptic vesicles into the surface membrane [CITATION_2] . In agreement with this hypothesis, our data demonstrate that in eosinophils, staurosporine retards fusion pore expansion in PMA-treated cells. This indicates that the effect of staurosporine on the exocytotic fusion pore may indeed be mediated by kinase inhibition. Although fusion pore expansion can be affected by staurosporine treatment, we found that in eosinophils, pore expansion and irreversible fusion still occur in its presence.",
